        "summary": "Avalo Therapeutics reported its first quarter 2026 financial results and provided business updates. A major highlight was the positive topline results from the Phase 2 LOTUS trial of abdakibart in patients with moderate to severe hidradenitis suppurativa (HS), where it met the primary endpoint of HiSCR75 at Week 16. The company also announced plans to advance abdakibart into a registrational Phase 3 program and highlighted a successful public offering of $431.3 million. As of March 31, 2026, Avalo had $82.0 million in cash, which does not include the subsequent financing proceeds expected to fund operations into 2029.",
